# Ad Click Prediction System — ML System Design

---

## 1. Problem Statement

Design an ML system that predicts the probability that a user will click on a given ad. This predicted Click-Through Rate (pCTR) is used to rank ads in real time and decide which ad to serve to a user.

**Core ML Task:** Binary Classification  
**Output:** pCTR ∈ [0, 1] — probability that a user clicks on an ad

---

## 2. Requirements

### 2.1 Functional Requirements

- Given a user and a set of candidate ads, return a ranked list of ads ordered by predicted click probability
- Support real-time inference — prediction must be served within the ad auction pipeline
- Re-train the model periodically to capture evolving user behavior and ad trends
- Log all impressions, clicks, and non-clicks for training data collection
- Support A/B testing to compare model versions before full rollout

### 2.2 Non-Functional Requirements

- **Latency:** End-to-end prediction under 100ms at p99 (ads must be ranked before the page loads)
- **Throughput:** Handle 500K–1M prediction requests per second at peak
- **Availability:** 99.99% uptime — a serving outage directly loses revenue
- **Scalability:** System must scale horizontally as traffic grows
- **Consistency:** Slight staleness in features (a few minutes) is acceptable; strong consistency not required
- **Fault Tolerance:** Fallback to a simpler model or rule-based ranking if ML service is down

