## 4. Data Collection & Labeling

### 4.1 Label Definition

| Event | Label |
|---|---|
| User clicks on ad | `y = 1` (positive) |
| Ad shown, no click (within 30s window) | `y = 0` (negative) |

**Label delay:** Clicks can arrive seconds to minutes after impression. A time window (e.g., 30 seconds to 1 hour) is defined. This creates a **delayed feedback problem** — recent data may have incomplete labels.

### 4.2 Data Sources

- **Impression logs:** ad_id, user_id, timestamp, features used at serving time
- **Click logs:** ad_id, user_id, click_timestamp
- **User activity logs:** browsing history, search queries, past purchases
- **Ad metadata:** advertiser, category, format, bid price, historical CTR

### 4.3 Class Imbalance

Only ~1–5% of impressions result in a click. Strategies to handle this:

- **Negative downsampling:** Randomly drop ~90–99% of negative examples during training. Adjust predicted probabilities at serving time using calibration correction: `p_corrected = p / (p + (1-p)/w)` where `w` is the downsampling rate
- **Weighted loss function:** Assign higher weight to positive class in the loss function
- **Evaluation on full data:** Always evaluate on the full unsampled dataset to get unbiased metrics

---

## 5. Feature Engineering

### 5.1 Feature Categories

**User Features**
- Demographics: age bucket, gender, location (country, city)
- Device: device type, OS, browser
- Behavioral: past CTR (last 1d / 7d / 30d), categories clicked, avg session length
- Temporal: hour of day, day of week

**Ad Features**
- Ad category, subcategory
- Advertiser ID
- Ad format (banner, video, native)
- Historical CTR of the ad (last 1d / 7d / 30d)
- Bid price

**User × Ad Interaction Features (Cross Features)**
- User category affinity × Ad category (did user previously click ads in this category?)
- User device × Ad format (video ads perform differently on mobile vs desktop)
- Time of day × Ad category

**Context Features**
- Page/placement where ad is shown
- Position on page (position bias — top positions get more clicks regardless of relevance)

### 5.2 Feature Storage

| Feature type | Storage | Update frequency |
|---|---|---|
| Real-time user features (last 1hr clicks) | Redis (in-memory) | Streaming, near real-time |
| Historical user aggregates (7d, 30d) | Feature store (e.g., Feast + DynamoDB) | Batch, daily |
| Ad metadata + historical CTR | Key-value store (DynamoDB) | Hourly |
| Static features (demographics) | Feature store, cached | Daily |

