## 7. Training Pipeline

```
Raw impression + click logs (S3 / HDFS)
          ↓
Spark batch job: join impressions with clicks, generate labels
          ↓
Feature extraction + joining with feature store snapshots
          ↓
Negative downsampling (keep 100% positives, 10% negatives)
          ↓
Train / Validation / Test split (time-based — DO NOT shuffle chronologically)
          ↓
Model training (LightGBM or Deep CTR model)
          ↓
Offline evaluation (AUC-ROC, Log Loss, calibration check)
          ↓
If metrics pass threshold → push to model registry (MLflow / SageMaker)
          ↓
Shadow mode deployment → compare with current production model offline
          ↓
A/B test in production → promote if online metrics improve
```

**Important:** Always use a **time-based split** (train on past, test on future). Never use random shuffle — that causes data leakage and inflates offline metrics.

**Retraining cadence:** Daily full retrain + hourly fine-tuning on recent data to handle trend drift.

