## 8. Serving / Inference Architecture

### 8.1 Request Flow

```
1. Ad request arrives (user opens page)
2. Candidate generation layer retrieves top N candidate ads (100–500)
3. Feature server fetches real-time user features from Redis
4. Feature server fetches ad features from DynamoDB
5. Features assembled → sent to ML inference service
6. Model scores all candidates in a single batched forward pass
7. Scores returned → ads ranked → top K selected
8. Ad shown to user; impression event logged asynchronously
```

### 8.2 Latency Budget (100ms total)

| Step | Budget |
|---|---|
| Network + routing | ~5ms |
| Candidate retrieval | ~10ms |
| Feature fetching (Redis + DynamoDB) | ~10–15ms |
| ML model inference | ~20–30ms |
| Ranking + auction logic | ~5ms |
| Response + rendering | ~10ms |

### 8.3 Inference Optimizations

- **Batch scoring:** Score all candidates in a single batched call, not one by one
- **Model quantization (INT8):** Reduce model size and speed up inference with minimal accuracy loss
- **ONNX / TorchScript export:** Serve models in optimized runtime
- **Caching:** Cache predictions for (user, ad) pairs seen very recently
- **Feature pre-fetching:** Start fetching features in parallel with candidate retrieval

