## 10. Offline Evaluation Metrics

| Metric | Why it matters |
|---|---|
| **AUC-ROC** | Measures ranking quality — can the model rank clicked ads above non-clicked ads? |
| **Log Loss (Cross-Entropy)** | Measures calibration — are predicted probabilities accurate? |
| **Normalized Cross-Entropy (NCE)** | Log loss normalized by the baseline model (prior CTR). NCE > 1 means our model is better than just predicting the average CTR |
| **Calibration Plot** | Plot predicted probability bins vs actual click rate — should be a diagonal line |
| **Precision @ K** | Of the top K ads ranked, how many actually got clicked? |

**Do NOT use accuracy** — with 99% negatives, a model that always predicts 0 gets 99% accuracy but is useless.

---

## 11. Online Evaluation Metrics

| Metric | Description |
|---|---|
| **CTR (Click-Through Rate)** | Clicks / Impressions — primary business metric |
| **RPM (Revenue per Mille)** | Revenue per 1000 impressions |
| **CVR (Conversion Rate)** | Post-click conversions (purchases, signups) |
| **p99 Latency** | Tail latency of inference service |
| **Model staleness** | Time since last retrain — monitor for concept drift |

