## 12. Monitoring & Alerting

### 12.1 Data Quality Monitoring
- Feature distribution drift (PSI — Population Stability Index) between training and serving
- Missing feature rate per feature — alert if > 5% nulls appear suddenly
- Label delay monitoring — alert if click join rate drops (may indicate logging failure)

### 12.2 Model Performance Monitoring
- **Online AUC:** Computed on a held-out slice of live traffic daily
- **CTR degradation:** Alert if CTR drops > 10% compared to 7-day rolling average
- **Prediction distribution shift:** Monitor histogram of predicted pCTR over time

### 12.3 Infrastructure Monitoring
- Inference latency (p50, p95, p99)
- Feature store read latency and error rate
- Kafka consumer lag (indicates feedback loop delays)
- Model serving throughput (QPS) and error rate

### 12.4 Alerting Thresholds

| Signal | Alert condition |
|---|---|
| p99 latency | > 150ms |
| Feature missing rate | > 5% for any critical feature |
| Online AUC | Drops > 2% vs baseline |
| CTR | Drops > 10% vs 7-day average |
| Model age | > 48 hours without successful retrain |

